                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/1578: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-22T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 22, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>141. Reference is to my No. 140 of May 21, 7 p.m., and to your No. 157, May 21, 9
                        p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d306fn27">Latter not printed.</note> Please delay
                    speaking to the Prime Minister about the suggestions contained in my telegram. I
                    think your discussion with the Prime Minister might well be postponed until
                    Marriner reviews the situation with you as he will at the first convenient
                    opportunity after his arrival in Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
